# FranklinOps / Trinity — Cursor Rules

## Code Quality
- Use type hints on all public functions
- Add docstrings to modules, classes, and public functions
- Prefer dataclasses over dicts for structured data
- Use `__all__` in modules to define public API

## Flow Interface
- Flow IDs: `[a-z][a-z0-9_-]*`, max 64 chars
- Handlers must return `dict` (never None)
- All flows pass through hardening: sanitize, rate limit, circuit breaker, retry, audit

## Security
- Never commit credentials; use env vars or keyring
- Sanitize all user input before processing
- Audit every flow invocation and governance decision

## Migrations
- Idempotent: handle "duplicate column", "already exists"
- One logical change per migration
- Use `INSERT OR IGNORE` for _migrations table

## Testing
- Run `python scripts/verify_integration.py` before commits
- Flow tests in verification: plug, invoke, hardening
